=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_BinaryOpUGen_ex2 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright pure_tone sound, with sine_like oscillator character around 329 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 328.6761
  harmonic_decay_rate: -3.4033
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9476
  pitch_clarity: 15.8567
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: sine_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -13.7045
  resonance_freq: 301.4648

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: BinaryOpUGen Example 2
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/BinaryOpUGen.html
// Tags: BinaryOpUGen, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 2 ---
a = WhiteNoise.ar; // a WhiteNoise
b = a + 2; // a BinaryOpUGen.
b.operator; // +

// sound example
(
{
    var a = LFSaw.ar(300);
    var b = LFSaw.ar(329.1);
    a % b * 0.1
}.play;
)
